197 initiative, a statewide effort to advance Alzheimer's
198 prevention research directly serving Alabamians through
199 education, clinical innovation, community engagement and
200 workforce development. The program will uncover new insights
201 for how Alzheimer's develops and use those findings to improve
202 how prevention is taught, how care is delivered, and how
203 families manage their brain health in Alabama. Thousands of
204 Alabama residents may volunteer to be screened to learn their
205 risk factors and receive personalized prevention guidance.
206 These discoveries will shape clinical practice, educate
207 Alabamians, strengthen and develop Alabama's biomedical
208 workforce, and further position the state as a national leader
209 to attract investment in healthcare research and prevention.
