285 Center; and $1,200,000 shall be used for the facilities grant
286 program. The Council of the Arts may award grants from the
287 facilities grant program for projects that build, renovate,
288 restore, preserve, or enhance arts facilities in Alabama,
289 including performing arts centers, art museums and galleries,
290 multi-purpose arts centers, artist residency facilities, and
291 outdoor performance venues. The Council of the Arts shall
292 emphasize rural assistance with grants, with a preference for
293 entities not receiving grants in the prior year. Eligible
294 entities include: (i) 501(c) (3) nonprofit arts organizations
295 chartered in Alabama, active and in good standing with the
296 Internal Revenue Service and the council; or (ii) an entity of
297 local government. Grant amounts shall not exceed $100,000 to
298 any one entity, with the first two grants being reserved for
299 the Arts Council of the Trussville Area Theater for $75,000
300 and the Carnegie Visual Arts Center for $100,000.
